#Take three numbers as input representing the sides of a triangle. First, check if a triangle with those sides can actually exist. If yes, compute the area. If no, say so clearly.

a = int(input("enter the first number"))
b = int(input("enter the second number"))
c = int(input("enter the third number"))
s = (a+b+c)/2
area = (s*(s-a)*(s-b)*(s-c))**0.5

if a+b>c and b+c>a and c+a>b:
    print("its a triangle",area)
else :
    print("its not a triangle")  






